<h1 class="bac"><%=program.Item("title")%></h1>

<div class="expanded">
<% call expandableH2("our_business", true) %>
<div>
<p class="bac">Global Markets Operations and Middle Office (GMO&amp;MO) provides controlled and cost effective post&ndash;trade processes in support of our Capital Markets, Corporate Investments, Corporate Treasury, Global Wealth and Investment Management, and Global Securities Services businesses.  The GMO&amp;MO group operates in 28 countries and has a significant presence in Charlotte, Chester, Chicago, Dublin, Hong Kong, Houston, Hyderabad, Jacksonville, London, New York and Singapore.</p>
<p class="bac nobr">Core functions include:</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Post&ndash;trade confirmation, settlement and client services processes</li>
	<li>Assurance over data and processes used to record risk, P/L, balance sheet and financial results</li>
</ul>
<p class="bac">The organization is comprised of two operating groups: <strong>Global Markets Operations</strong> and <strong>Global Middle Office</strong>.  A change management team is responsible for the successful execution of prioritized change initiatives.</p>
<p class="bac"><strong>Global Markets Operations</strong> core processes include confirmation, settlement and clearing, and reconciliation processes. <strong>Global Middle Office</strong> processes include trade capture validation, risk and P&amp;L control, balance sheet control and front to back oversight. The organizational infrastructure has been designed to ensure global consistency of processes and a strong global and local supervision.</p>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<% call expandableH2("overview", false) %>
<div>
<p class="bac">This is a competitive one&ndash;year global Development Program designed to develop high potential graduates and facilitate your transition from academia to a professional career so you can hit the ground running from day one.  The 12&ndash;month program will provide you with the necessary tools to manage difficult challenges and be successful in this fast paced industry. Every analyst will receive program management support, structured learning and development training, the opportunity to engage in cross functional projects and networking opportunities.</p>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<% call expandableH2("qualifications", false) %>
<div>
<p class="bac nobr">Candidates must be a final year candidate from a four year college or university and demonstrate a combination of academic aptitude, quantitative skills, strategic and creative thinking, and excellent written and oral communication skills. Analysts will be required to manage several projects at once and work effectively both individually and as part of a team. Some common driving characteristics we look for:</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Attention to detail</li>
	<li>Exceptional academic achievement</li>
	<li>Initiative; team focus</li>
	<li>Leadership</li>
	<li>Strategic and creative thinking capabilities</li>
	<li>Strong work ethic</li>
	<li>Strong communication skills</li>
	<li>Dedication to a career in Middle Office or  Operations</li>
	<li>Ability to work in a fast&ndash;paced environment</li>
	<li>Geographic mobility</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<% call expandableH2("training", false) %>
<div>
<p class="bac">As a new analyst, you will begin your career at Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America with an extensive training program. Participants will attend orientation, which provides hands&ndash;on learning and development as well as professional skill building to position you for a successful career at Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America.</p>
<p class="bac">The one&ndash;year development program includes a comprehensive Learning Curriculum focused on business acumen, financial skills and soft skills, including leadership competencies. The Learning Curriculum is a combination of instructor&ndash;led training, virtual&ndash;led training, e&ndash;learning modules, case studies, and presentations.</p>
<p class="bac">Throughout the program, you&#39;ll have the opportunity to interact with senior management and executives during monthly or quarterly business overview sessions and/or networking opportunities that are developed specifically for the program.  As an analyst, you will work closely with teammates from across the globe, with many of the program activities and networking opportunities reflecting the global nature of our business.  This is a great opportunity to build a network of colleagues from across the company that will be a tremendous resource to you throughout your career.</p>
<p class="bac nobr">Analysts will also have the opportunity to participate in the Global Technology and Operations Mentor Program, which helps build your network, skills and core competencies through one&ndash;on&ndash;one interaction with leaders. It includes an innovative online tool for registration, matching and guidance on mentor relationship management.</p>
<p class="bac">To further support your professional development, we also have a formal Performance Management process, which is used to establish an individual&#39;s objectives and measure performance against those objectives throughout the year. It is also intended to serve as a tool to create open lines of communication between you and your manager and help you continuously develop and advance your career at Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America.</p>
</div></div>

